definition.value: A tripeptide comprising L-alanyl, gamma-D-glutamyl and meso-diaminopimelic acid residues in a linear sequence. It is a breakdown product of bacterial peptidoglycan and a NOD1 agonist.
A dipeptide consisting of L-glutamic acid having an L-alanyl attached to its alpha-amino group
A dipeptide consisting of D-glutamic acid having an L-alanyl attached to its alpha-amino group
The organophosphate oxoanion formed from D-hexopyranose 6-phosphate by loss of two protons from the phosphate group; principal species at pH 7.3.
A ketoaldonic acid comprising a 3-deoxyoctulosonic acid having beta-L-gulo-configuration.
A disaccharide comprising an alpha-3,4-dehydro-3,4,5-trideoxy-Kdo residue joined via a (2->8)-linkage to 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulopyranosonic acid (Kdo)
A carbohydrate acid comprising 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulopyranosonic acid (Kdo) having a 5-deoxy-4-epi-2,3-dehydro-Kdo moiety attached via an unusual (4->8) non-glycosidic linkage.
A disaccharide comprising 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulopyranose (Kdo-CH2OH) having a 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulopyranonosyl (Kdo) residue attached at the 4-position.
A glycosylglycerol in which the glycosyl moeity is any digalactosyl group.
A glycodihydroceramide having alpha-D-galactosyl component and the ceramide N-acyl group specified as tetradecanoyl.
D-glycero-D-manno-heptose 1-phosphate(2-) with alpha-configuration at the anomeric carbon atom.
A fucosyl oligoglycosylceramide consisting of ganglioside GM1 having an alpha-L-fucosyl residue attached at the 2-position of the galactose at the non-reducing end.
A glycopentaosylceramide having alpha-L-Fuc-(1->2)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the glycopentaosyl component.
A sialotetraosylceramide having beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->6)]-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the sialotetraosyl component.
A amino tetrasaccharide comprising D-GalNAc having a beta-D-GlcNAc residue at the 6-position and a alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal residue at the 3-position.
A linear amino trisaccharide comprising an alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl residue (2->3)-linked to a beta-D-galactosyl residue, which is in turn linked (1->3) to N-acetyl-D-galactosamine.
An amino disaccharide consisting of N-acetyl-D-galactosamine having a N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residue attached at the 6-position.
A branched amino trisaccharide comprising N-acetyl-D-galactose having a beta-D-galactosyl residue at the 3-position and a N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residue at the 6-position.
A fatty amide comprising nonadecanamide having tetradecyl, oxo and amino substituents at the 2-, 4- and 5-positions respectively.
A myo-inositol monophosphate derivative consisting of 1-O-(6-thiohexylphosphono)-D-myo-inositol having a 2-amino-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosyl residue at the 6-position.
A myo-inositol monophosphate derivative consisting of 1-O-(6-thiohexylphosphono)-D-myo-inositol having an alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-alpha-D-glucosaminyl residue at the 6-position.
A 2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucoside, being mycothiol substituted on sulfur by a hydroxymethyl group.

A myo-inositol monophosphate derivative consisting of 1-O-(6-thiohexylphosphono)-D-myo-inositol having an alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->6)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-alpha-D-glucosaminyl residue at the 6-position.

A myo-inositol monophosphate derivative consisting of 1-O-(6-thiohexylphosphono)-D-myo-inositol having an alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->6)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-alpha-D-glucosaminyl residue at the 6-position.
The lipid IVA oxoanion that is (KDO)-lipid IVA(5-) phosphorylated at the 4 position on the KDO moiety; protonated to pH 7.3.

A myo-inositol monophosphate derivative consisting of 1-O-(6-thiohexylphosphono)-D-myo-inositol having a 6-O-(2-aminoethylphosphono)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->6)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-alpha-D-glucosaminyl residue at the 6-position.

A myo-inositol monophosphate derivative consisting of 1-O-(6-thiohexylphosphono)-D-myo-inositol having an alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->6)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-alpha-D-glucosaminyl residue at the 6-position.

A myo-inositol monophosphate derivative consisting of 1-O-(6-thiohexylphosphono)-D-myo-inositol having an alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->2)-6-O-(2-aminoethylphosphono)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->6)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-alpha-D-glucosaminyl residue at the 6-position.
D-glycero-D-manno-heptose 1-phosphate(2-) with beta-configuration at the anomeric carbon atom.
A D-galactosyl-N-acylsphingosine where the ceramide N-acyl group is nonadecanoyl.
An aryl group obtained via removal of the hydrogen atom from the 4-position of nitrobenzene.
An amino disaccharide consisting of D-galactose having an alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl residue attached at the 3-position
An N-acetylated alpha-(2->8)-linked homosialopolysaccharide consisting of six alpha-D-N-acetylneuraminyl residues joined by (2->8) linkages (i.e. [8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->]n  where n = 6).
A polysaccharide composed of a backbone of alpha-D-fucosyl (1->2)-beta-L-rhamnosyl repeating units that are joined to each other via (1->3)-linkages.
An amino oligosaccharide consisting of repeating units of N-acetylneuraminic acid that are joined via alpha-(2->8)-linkages. Commonly known as polysialic acid or PSA,
An N-propionylated alpha-(2->8)-linked homosialopolysaccharide consisting of six alpha-D-N-propionylneuraminyl residues joined by (2->8) linkages (i.e. [8)-alpha-Neu5Pr-(2->]n  where n = 6).
A glucosamine oligosaccharide comprising N-acetylglucosamine at the reducing end having an alpha-L-rhamnosyl-(1->2)-alpha-L-rhamnosyl-(1->3)-alpha-L-rhamnosyl group attached at the 3-position.
A ten-membered glucosamine oligosaccharide comprising eight alpha-L-rhamnosyl residues (one at the reducing end) and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residues in a linear sequence.
A poly(alkylene oxide) polymer, composed of poly(butylene oxide) macromolecules.
A poly(ether) polymer, composed of poly[5-(4-benzoylphenoxy)-2-hydroxybenzenesulfonic acid] macromolecules.
A poly(ether) polymer, composed of poly(p-dioxane) macromolecules.
A glycosylglucose in which the glycosyl moiety is L-rhamnose linked alpha to C-6 of D-glucose.
A poly(ether) polymer composed of poly(p-dioxanone) macromolecules.
A poly(ether) polymer, composed of poly(vinyl methyl ether) macromolecules.
A glycosylmannose consisting of alpha-D-mannose having an alpha-D-mannosyl residue attached at the 2-position
A glycohexaosylceramide having beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the glycohexaosyl component.
A mannotriose consisting of three alpha-(1->6)-linked D-mannopyranose units with undefined stereochemistry at the reducing end.
A linear trisaccharide consisting of three D-mannose units joined by alpha-(1->2)- and alpha-(1->6)-linkages
A linear trisaccharide consisting of three D-mannose units joined by alpha-(1->2)-linkages
